videos.description: Ian Book rolls out and throws a 23-yard pass to Chase Claypool who stays in-bounds for extra yards.
videos.headline: Book connects with Claypool for big gain

videos.description: Ian Book finds Cameron Smith for a 6-yard touchdown to get Notre Dame on the board.
videos.headline: Book throws first career TD for Irish

videos.description: Josh Adams finds a hole and takes it 73 yards for a Notre Dame rushing touchdown.
videos.headline: Adams breaks free for huge TD

videos.description: Ian Book throws a long interception from his own end zone to Myles Dorn late in the first half.
videos.headline: Book picked off on deep throw

videos.description: Anthony Ratliff-Williams makes a fantastic catch in the back of the end zone for a 25-yard touchdown from Chazz Surratt.
videos.headline: UNC's Ratliff-Williams goes up for a great TD grab

videos.description: Jordon Brown tries to run it out of his own end zone but is swamped quickly for a safety at the end of the first half.
videos.headline: Brown tackled in end zone for Notre Dame safety

videos.description: Notre Dame head coach Brian Kelly  wants his  players to take some of the pressure off his back-up quarterback Ian Book.
videos.headline: Kelly wants other players to step up around Book

videos.description: The Fighting Irish used a strong defensive effort to build a 16-7 halftime lead on North Carolina.

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Highlight (Notre Dame leads UNC at half) 2017/10/07 ESHEET ENHL

videos.headline: Notre Dame leads UNC at half

videos.description: Notre Dame quarterback Ian Book is picked off in the red zone by Myles Dorn. Book's second interception of the game.
videos.headline: Book picked off in red zone

videos.description: Deon McIntosh takes it 35 yards for a touchdown increasing the Irish's lead to 26-7.
videos.headline: McIntosh adds to Notre Dame's lead

videos.description: Deon McIntosh finds room on the left for a 24-yard touchdown, his second of the day for Notre Dame.
videos.headline: McIntosh runs in his 2nd TD

videos.description: Notre Dame head coach Brian Kelly enjoyed his team's ability to control the game through their defense and offensive line in the Irish's 33-10 win over North Carolina.
videos.headline: Kelly: 'We controlled the 4th quarter'

videos.description: The No. 21 Fighting Irish rush for 341 yards and three scores en route to a 33-10 win on the road over the Tar Heels.
